Munich - A 90-year-old man has died following a confrontation in a retirement home in Germany, police and public prosecutors said on Monday.The man was taken to hospital on December 4 following a clash with another resident, 88, at the home in Breitenguessbach, near the Bavarian town of Bamberg.The 90-year-old was allegedly punched in the abdomen during the argument. He was taken to hospital after staff were alerted to the incident, but died two days later.The postmortem has now revealed broken ribs as the cause of death, the authorities said.The 88-year-old is being investigated for assault causing death.ANA-dpa